reviews.title: Recommend
reviews.text: I’ve flown with Delta numerous times and I’ve never had any issues. The flight attendants are kind and always helpful. I always carry a carryon and a personal item so that I never have to check my luggage. If open seats are available they will allow you to move so you don’t have to sit next to anyone. When you fly long distances they have free movies available, and their movie selection is perfect. I highly recommend flying with Delta!

reviews.title: Final leg home after a long International trip
reviews.text: Best legroom of my entire trip. Food/snack as decent, and was able to watch a movie. Plane seemed a bit cold, though.

reviews.title: Thoroughly enjoyable and comfortable flight
reviews.text: Flying Premium Economy, or Comfort-Plus seemed heavenly after a cramped flight prior to this one. Decent food, ample legroom, and nice entertainment featured.

reviews.title: Nice intercontinental flight.
reviews.text: If offered on your Delta flight, opt for premium economy called Comfort Plus. The seats aren't much wider but have more recline and better legroom than standard economy or main cabin.

reviews.title: Decent flight during holiday season; overbooked and fully packed airplane
reviews.text: This flight was aboard a Boeing 737-900, and was typical Boeing cramped seats with poor legroom. Thankfully, this was the first leg of an international flight to Vienna, Austria. Clean airplane, attentive attendants, but didn't make up for a basically uncomfortable airplane in standard main cabin economy.
